\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 ## 2026-03-14 | CLI vs GUI trade-offs \'97 choosing Claude Code over Claude Desktop\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **What happened**: Chose Claude Code (CLI) as my primary development tool instead of Claude Desktop (GUI app). Claude Code runs in the terminal and connects to external systems through MCP servers. Claude Desktop is a visual chat window with no programmatic integrations.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **What I learned**: CLI tools compose \'97 you can pipe output, script them, chain them with other tools, and integrate them into automated workflows. GUI tools are easier to learn initially but become bottlenecks when you need automation. This is the same reason production servers run headless Linux (no desktop environment): the GUI provides convenience but consumes resources and can't be scripted. Claude Code's real power is the MCP layer \'97 it can talk to GitHub, AWS, and other services directly, which a GUI chat window can't do.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **Design principle**: Composability over convenience \'97 choose tools that integrate with other tools, even if the initial learning curve is steeper. In software architecture, this shows up as preferring APIs over dashboards, microservices over monoliths, and event-driven systems over synchronous calls.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **Interview version**: "I chose Claude Code over the desktop GUI because I needed composability. Claude Code connects to GitHub and AWS through MCP servers, meaning the AI can take real actions on my infrastructure \'97 create repos, deploy Lambda functions, query DynamoDB \'97 all from one terminal session. It's the same principle behind why production systems use CLIs over dashboards: they compose into automated workflows."\cb1 \
