\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## 2026-03-14 | Project scoping and defense in depth for AI coding assistants\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **What happened**: Before letting Claude Code modify any files, I set up three layers of protection: physical scoping (only launching from the project directory), a CLAUDE.md config file with explicit boundaries, and keeping the default permission mode where every file write requires my approval.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **What I learned**: This is defense in depth \'97 the same security architecture used in production systems. No single control is sufficient on its own. A firewall doesn't replace IAM policies, and IAM policies don't replace application-level auth. You layer them. For AI-assisted development specifically, the risk is the AI modifying files outside your project scope or running destructive commands. Three independent controls make accidental damage very unlikely. Git as a safety net (commit before letting the AI work, use `git diff` to review changes) adds a fourth layer.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **Design principle**: Defense in depth \'97 layer multiple independent security controls so that the failure of any single control doesn't compromise the system. Each layer catches what the previous one might miss.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **Interview version**: "I implemented defense in depth for my AI-assisted development workflow. The AI tool operates within three concentric security boundaries: physical directory scoping, a project-level config file with explicit constraints, and a permission system requiring manual approval for every file modification. I also use git as a fourth safety net \'97 committing before AI sessions so I can diff and revert any unintended changes."\cb1 \
